All Implemented Interfaces:
org.eclipse.jface.dialogs.IDialogPage, org.eclipse.jface.dialogs.IMessageProvider, org.eclipse.jface.wizard.IWizardPage
public class NewProjectWizardPage
extends org.eclipse.ui.dialogs.WizardNewProjectCreationPage

A class that creates a new Google Data wizard page. It allows setting the new Google Data project name, select the project template and provide the dependency path. It also provides the third party dependency options.

Author:
kunalshah@google.com (Kunal Shah)

Constructor Detail

NewProjectWizardPage

public NewProjectWizardPage(java.lang.String pageName,
                            java.lang.String title,
                            java.lang.String description,
                            org.eclipse.jface.resource.ImageDescriptor image,
                            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,FileTemplateConfig> templateConfigMap)
Creates a new Google Data Project Wizard Page.

If title is null, then it won't be displayed.

If description is null, then it won't be displayed.

If image is null, then it won't be displayed.

Parameters:
pageName - the name of this page
title - the title of this page
description - the description of this page
image - the image to be displayed on this page's title bar
templateConfigMap - the Map of template configuration elements
